MY LIL DUDE tracked along the inside, chased around the far turn and faded. STONE ALLIANCE stalked three to two wide, then between horses down the backstretch and faded. ROCK STAR ALEX laid off of the pace in the four to five path and failed to factor on his left lead. MAIN DUDE sternly pressed the leader around the first turn, chased that one down the backstretch, but began to weaken with a half mile to go and was eased through the lane.
